public class IllegalAssignmentError
extends java.lang.Error

The exception thrown on an attempt to make an illegal assignment. For example, this will be thrown if logic attempts to assign a reference to an object in ScopedMemory to a field in an object in ImmortalMemory. All Implemented Interfaces: java.io.Serializable
